title: For Sale:  Rasheed Egyptian 7.62 X 39 Carbine-Rare import for the military collector
postcontent:
Collectors piece- Rasheed (AKA Rashid) 7.62 X 39 Carbine made for the Egyptian military by the U.A.R. (United Arab Republic). There were only 8000 of these rifles made between 1966-1968 as per my research; as the Egyptian army switched over to the AK platform. I have only found numbers ranging between 2000 to 3000 being imported to the U.S.- Thus the rarity.
These are the Arab SKS "Wannabe" models with full wood, threaded muzzle and the knife bayonet. Comes with a removeable 10 round magazine, but made to be used with 10 round stripper clips. Everyone who I have had contact with who has owned a Rasheed has wished they never sold the one they had --- so that speaks loads to the popularity of these Carbines. 
The carbine has a rear safety and a trigger that has the feel of a custom gunsmith job. 
Feel free to write with questions and I can send more pictures.
Selling for cash only, no trades on this gem.
Sale to Oregon residents 18 and over willing to sign a Bill of Sale.
Thank you for looking!
$750

title: For Sale/Trade:  Kommer Waffenfabrik GmbH, Zella Mehlis.
postcontent:
Kommer Waffenfabrik GmbH, Zella Mehlis. 32ACP! 
 According to 'Pistols of the World' Theodor Kommer made Four models were eventualy produced, all based on Browning designs. The first three copied the Mod. 1906, the last was based on the 1910. 
... only some of those had the name Kommer on the grips (most just had "Th K" in an oval. ...all Kommer production ceased in 1940."

 produced by Theodor Kommer Waffenfabrik GmbH, Zella Mehlis. It is almost an exact copy of the Belgian, FN Browning Model 1910. 
the Kommer Model 4 is not a commonly encountered pistol,German police and civil guard were known to carry as well as some officers.
 production about 1936 and ceased in 1940 with only a small quantity made during this period. A very difficult pistol to locate for ones collection. Right slide is blank.  Left side is stamped: Waffen Fabrik Kommer Zella-Mehlis Kal 7.65 (Zella-Mehlis was also the home of the Walther factory) Only other markings on handgun is the serial # on left trigger guard: 15,xxx  Eagle over N proof (used after 4/1/1940 throughout WWII). Of interest there are sights both intact front and rear with grooving running down top of the slide.  A left rear safety.  The magazine has a rear knurled clasp to release. pistol is in fair shape with slight pitting and wear on the slide only!!! . the bore is very bright, with very clean internals with hardly any wear, as if the pistol had sweat in a leather holster for years and hardly been shot. I have fired 2 magazines without a hiccup. crisp clean action! the pistol comes with two original magazines. prime example of a wartime nazi pistol, not many produced,,rare!!!! clearing out some wartime and pre war relic pistols, no trades accepted at this time.
last two of these i saw sold on guns america for 975 and one for 600 +shipping & transfer fees.........REDACTED email call or text
